.TH "TASKSIGNAL.ANY_STATIC" "3JS" "July 28, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TaskSignal.any_static \- TaskSignal: any() static method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]TaskSignal.any()\f[B]\f[R] static method takes an
iterable of \f[CR]AbortSignal\f[R] objects and returns a
\f[CR]TaskSignal\f[R].
The returned task signal is aborted when any of the abort signals is
aborted.
.PP
When the task signal is aborted, its \f[CR]reason\f[R] property will be
set to the reason of the first signal that is aborted.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
TaskSignal.any(signals)
TaskSignal.any(signals, init)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]signals\f[R]
An iterable (such as an \f[CR]Array\f[R]) of abort signals.
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
Contains optional configuration parameters.
Currently only one property is defined:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]priority\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
One of the following:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
A priority string which is one of \f[CR]user\-blocking\f[R],
\f[CR]user\-visible\f[R] and \f[CR]background\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
A \f[CR]TaskSignal\f[R].
.RE
.RE
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]TaskSignal\f[R] instance.
It will be aborted when the first signal passed into \f[CR]signals\f[R]
is aborted.
When this happens:
.IP \(bu 2
Its \f[CR]reason\f[R] property will be set to the reason of the signal
that caused this signal to abort.
.IP \(bu 2
Its \f[CR]priority\f[R] property will be determined by the
\f[CR]priority\f[R] parameter:
.RS 2
.IP \(bu 2
If the \f[CR]priority\f[R] parameter was a string, it will be the value
of the string.
.IP \(bu 2
If the \f[CR]priority\f[R] parameter was a \f[CR]TaskSignal\f[R], it
will be the value of that signal\(cqs \f[CR]priority\f[R].
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using \f[CR]TaskSignal.any()\f[R]
This example demonstrates combining both a signal from a
\f[CR]TaskController\f[R], and a timeout signal from
\f[CR]TaskSignal.timeout()\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] cancelDownloadButton = document.getElementById(\(dqcancelDownloadButton\(dq);

\f[B]const\f[R] userCancelController = \f[B]new\f[R] TaskController({
  priority: \(dquser\-visible\(dq,
});

cancelDownloadButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  userCancelController.abort();
});

\f[I]// Timeout after 5 minutes\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] timeoutSignal = TaskSignal.timeout(1_000 * 60 * 5);

\f[I]// This signal will abort when either the user clicks the cancel button or 5 minutes is up whichever is sooner\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] combinedSignal = TaskSignal.any([
  userCancelController.signal,
  timeoutSignal,
]);

\f[B]try\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] res = \f[B]await\f[R] fetch(someUrlToDownload, {
    \f[I]// Stop the fetch when any of the\f[R]
    signal: combinedSignal,
  });
  \f[B]const\f[R] body = \f[B]await\f[R] res.blob();
  \f[I]// Do something with downloaded content\f[R]
  \f[I]// \&...\f[R]
} \f[B]catch\f[R] (e) {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (e.name === \(dqAbortError\(dq) {
    \f[I]// Cancelled by the user\f[R]
  } \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (e.name === \(dqTimeoutError\(dq) {
    \f[I]// Show user that download timed out\f[R]
  } \f[B]else\f[R] {
    \f[I]// Other error, e.g. network error\f[R]
  }
}
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]AbortSignal.any()\f[R]
